<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 8:13AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow to impact Helena and locations along
Canyon Ferry Lake through early this afternoon...
Localized heavy bands of snow will impact the Helena area and
locations along Canyon Ferry Lake through early this afternoon.
Visibility will range from 1 mile to as low as a quarter mile
while snow is falling. Road surfaces should remain wet, but the
heavy bands will cause slushy snow to accumulate at times,
especially over bridges and over passes.
Anyone traveling should expect reduced visibility and potentially
slippery roads due to slushy snow accumulation and or ponding of
water.</description>
